    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Copper-zinc-tin alloy, sometimes also including lead, made by melting ground calamine ore with charcoal and copper; used in the Medieval period for weights and utensils.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aleación de cobre-zinc-estaño, que a veces incluye plomo, obtenida al fundir mineral de calamina triturado con carbón y cobre. Se utilizaba en el período medieval para pesos y utensilios.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een legering van koper, zink en tin, soms ook wel met lood. Het wordt gemaakt door gemalen kalamijnerts met houtskool en koper te smelten; werd in de Middeleeuwen gebruikt voor gewichten en gereedschap.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>銅、鋅、錫之合金，有時也含鉛，是將磨碎的異極礦石與木炭和銅一起熔化製成；中世紀時用來製作度量衡用具及器皿。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
